{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782079249,"nonce":"8rAcVKDqqLiMqFbgx7x46IjsWwk=","title":"**Summary**","message":"Map fixed-size byte arrays (`[u8; N]`) to a binary column so hashes / keys / wrapped\nDEKs can be stored with a known width.\n\n**Motivation**\nThe sealed-secrets use case (and crypto generally) deals in fixed-width byte arrays —\n32-byte keys, digests, nonces. Today only variable-length `Vec\u003cu8\u003e` (`bytea`/`BLOB`)\nis supported (git-bug ed37021); a `C::Type\u003c'scope, [u8; 32]\u003e` column does not bind.\n\n**Scope**\n- v1: `[u8; N]` (and `Option\u003c[u8; N]\u003e`) column binding + codec.\n- Decide DDL: PostgreSQL has no fixed-length binary, so it would render `bytea`\n  (length enforced in Rust on decode, optionally a CHECK); MySQL maps to `BINARY(N)`.\n\n**Plan**\n- Const-generic binding impls mirroring the `Vec\u003cu8\u003e` work: `HasColumnType` /\n  `ColumnNullability` / `ExprKind` for `[u8; N]` (likely `impl\u003cconst N: usize\u003e`),\n  plus `IntoAssignmentValue` / `IntoExpr` and per-backend `Encode`/`Decode`\n  (`Decode` length-checks the column, erroring on a width mismatch).\n- A new `ColumnType`/`SqlType` may be needed if `BINARY(N)` should round-trip through\n  introspection with its length (otherwise reuse `Bytes` and accept widening).\n\n**Files**\ncrates/squealy/src/column.rs, expr.rs, query.rs; both backends' query.rs + sql.rs\n(DDL); crates/squealy-test; + tests.\n\n**Tests**\nBind/render `[u8; 32]` + `Option\u003c[u8; N]\u003e`; codec round-trip; decode rejects a\nwrong-length value; DDL renders `bytea` (PG) / `BINARY(N)` (MySQL).\n\n**Size**\nMedium (const generics + a possible new SqlType for the fixed width).\n\n**Acceptance**\nA `[u8; N]` column compiles in insert/where/select and round-trips; mismatched width\nfails to decode cleanly.\n\n**Depends on**\ned37021 (Vec\u003cu8\u003e/bytea binding) — landed.","files":null}]}